cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper uses machine learning and natural language processing techniques to analyze Yelp reviews and extract information about specific aspects of restaurants, such as environment, service, and flavor. This falls under the categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR), as the paper involves analyzing text data to extract meaningful information. The use of support vector machines (SVMs) also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper's emphasis on characterizing different types of restaurants based on customer reviews could also fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
